Playing matchmaker for their love.

296
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,440
The director said,

297
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:30,440
this Nurse to Juliet you're playing,

298
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,840
for the sake of their love,

299
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,639
threads the needle,

300
00:11:35,039 --> 00:11:37,220
and helps move things along.

301
00:11:37,759 --> 00:11:38,539
It's basically Wang Po.

302
00:11:46,059 --> 00:11:46,600
Yingzi!

303
00:11:47,059 --> 00:11:47,580
Yingzi!

304
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:48,460
Auntie Cai is looking for you.

305
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,340
My hands are full right now.

306
00:11:51,059 --> 00:11:51,860
Go quickly.

307
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,100
The old lady is asking everyone.

308
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:54,059
Seems pretty urgent.

309
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,580
What's it about?

310
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:57,000
She's looked for me several times.

311
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:00,580
It must be...

312
00:12:00,899 --> 00:12:01,340
Alright.

313
00:12:01,340 --> 00:12:02,480
I got it, I'm going.

314
00:12:05,139 --> 00:12:05,659
Wait.

315
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,860
Do you know what it is?

316
00:12:09,399 --> 00:12:11,379
Isn't it just Auntie Cai trying to set me up

317
00:12:11,379 --> 00:12:12,659
with Rudy's nephew?

318
00:12:23,419 --> 00:12:24,419
The One I Like

319
00:12:24,419 --> 00:12:25,919
Director Hans hopes

320
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:26,820
we

321
00:12:27,019 --> 00:12:28,039
in this

322
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:29,879
production of *Romeo and Juliet*,

323
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:33,240
can incorporate more Chinese elements.

324
00:12:34,759 --> 00:12:37,200
We welcome your very valuable opinions.

325
00:12:37,259 --> 00:12:37,740
Or...

326
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,820
your not-so-valuable opinions.

327
00:12:39,899 --> 00:12:41,960
Then let me offer a not-so-valuable opinion first.

328
00:12:42,039 --> 00:12:45,120
You see, for my role as the Nurse,

329
00:12:45,159 --> 00:12:47,720
can we not follow the style of Wang Po?

330
00:12:47,919 --> 00:12:49,639
In our Chinese opera,

331
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:50,879
there is a character called Hongniang.

332
00:12:50,879 --> 00:12:51,360
Right.

333
00:12:51,419 --> 00:12:52,100
A young maiden role.

334
00:12:52,159 --> 00:12:52,820
Exactly.

335
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:54,700
As soon as she gets on stage, she goes...

336
00:12:55,059 --> 00:12:58,379
"Early in the morning, I drew a wild card."

337
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,940
That's not Peking Opera!

338
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:02,120
You're playing Mahjong!

339
00:13:03,919 --> 00:13:05,980
The director has said,

340
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:08,019
we can try anything.

341
00:13:08,019 --> 00:13:10,399
If we can open up our thinking that much,

342
00:13:10,399 --> 00:13:12,740
then for my role, Cui Yingying's father,

343
00:13:12,799 --> 00:13:14,840
I can play him like the Old Yuanwai.

344
00:13:15,139 --> 00:13:17,179
Who is Old Yuanwai?

345
00:13:17,659 --> 00:13:19,299
Is Old Yuanwai here today?

346
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,740
Old Yuanwai is Cui Yingying's father.

347
00:13:23,139 --> 00:13:24,480
In your play, that's the Old Count.

348
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:27,179
*Romance of the West Chamber*. Never heard of it?

349
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:29,360
If that's the case,

350
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,179
I'll write and perform a piece myself.

351
00:13:31,179 --> 00:13:31,759
How about that?

352
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:32,600
Good.

353
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,639
Let me know if it's good or not.

354
00:13:33,639 --> 00:13:34,139
Okay?

355
00:13:34,139 --> 00:13:35,360
Okay.

356
00:13:38,639 --> 00:13:40,620
He's about to start singing.

357
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:44,740
In days past, my fine youth flowed away like water.

358
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,419
Sighing at life... Which play is this?

359
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,659
I don't know.

360
00:13:48,399 --> 00:13:49,480
*Temple of Eight Gods*?

361
00:13:50,299 --> 00:13:51,539
I didn't say that.

362
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:52,559
With *Capture Alive*?

363
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,980
Who are you capturing alive?

364
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:58,759
*The Real and Fake Li Kui*?

365
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,580
Stop shouting.

366
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:02,259
*Black Cat Detective*.

367
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:03,139
Then...

368
00:14:03,139 --> 00:14:04,620
how does that go?

369
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:10,860
Peerless tenderness.

370
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:13,299
Bravo!

371
00:14:13,299 --> 00:14:14,299
Great!

372
00:14:15,419 --> 00:14:17,139
That was sung beautifully!

373
00:14:17,659 --> 00:14:19,639
I didn't understand a word.

374
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:24,159
That wasn't *Black Cat Detective*!

375
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:27,000
Isn't this *Romance of the West Chamber*?

376
00:14:27,179 --> 00:14:28,539
An old play.

377
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:31,940
He sang the part of Cui Yingying's father.

378
00:14:32,139 --> 00:14:34,120
Cui Yingying's father is dead!

379
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:35,519
You're confused again.

380
00:14:36,059 --> 00:14:37,580
I am not confused.

381
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:40,299
It's from *Romance of the West Chamber*,

382
00:14:40,299 --> 00:14:42,539
the part the Old Yuanwai sings.

383
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:45,840
That Old Yuanwai is Cui Yingying's father!

384
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,759
She went down the mountain with Liang Shanbo.

385
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:50,100
And returned to life.

386
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:50,919
In the end,

387
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,360
that's the part he was singing.

388
00:14:52,399 --> 00:14:54,559
In the end, he sang Liang Shanbo to death.

389
00:15:23,379 --> 00:15:23,899
Yingzi

390
00:15:25,019 --> 00:15:25,879
Auntie Cai...

391
00:15:26,679 --> 00:15:28,519
introduced you to that Parched guy?

392
00:15:28,779 --> 00:15:29,799
Yeah, she did.

393
00:15:32,220 --> 00:15:33,220
So you've met?

394
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,720
If she introduced us, of course we've met.

395
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:38,940
Do you...

396
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:40,279
think he's okay?

397
00:15:40,919 --> 00:15:43,000
I think he's pretty good.

398
00:15:43,159 --> 00:15:44,100
He's quite interesting.

399
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,480
Then what does he think of you?

400
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:48,679
He thinks I'm pretty good too.

401
00:15:48,879 --> 00:15:50,740
Says I meet his requirements.

402
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:57,759
You're not eating?

403
00:15:58,899 --> 00:15:59,700
I can't eat anymore.

404
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:07,379
Here, let me take that.

405
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,059
Thanks, Zhuzhu.

406
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:14,980
Why...

407
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:16,639
why hasn't the show started yet?

408
00:16:16,639 --> 00:16:17,600
It's over.

409
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:23,179
Take it easy.

410
00:16:23,759 --> 00:16:24,600
Yusheng.

411
00:16:24,879 --> 00:16:26,480
Don't be too upset.

412
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:28,799
The two of them just have a good impression of each other.

413
00:16:28,919 --> 00:16:30,919
But they definitely won't end up together.

414
00:16:31,039 --> 00:16:32,879
Even if they do end up together,

415
00:16:33,039 --> 00:16:34,480
theirs is a transnational romance.

416
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,700
It definitely won't last long.

417
00:16:35,899 --> 00:16:37,100
Even if it lasts long,

418
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:40,080
they definitely won't walk down the aisle.

419
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,960
Even if they walk down the aisle,

420
00:16:42,179 --> 00:16:43,899
they definitely won't grow old together.

421
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,000
Even if... Stop.

422
00:16:45,679 --> 00:16:47,159
Are you trying to comfort me?

423
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,940
You've planned their lives out to 2070.

424
00:16:50,179 --> 00:16:50,860
No,

425
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:52,679
that's just what I mean.

426
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:53,379
Look,

427
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,860
Romeo and Juliet.

428
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,899
Were they in love?

429
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,000
Was their love deep?

430
00:16:59,580 --> 00:17:00,440
Was it solid?

431
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:01,480
And what was the result?

432
00:17:01,539 --> 00:17:03,179
Didn't they die in the end?

433
00:17:04,619 --> 00:17:05,740
You mean,

434
00:17:06,099 --> 00:17:07,339
Yingzi is Juliet,

435
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,180
and Parched is Romeo?

436
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:10,460
Then what about me?

437
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,400
I'm the one waiting to collect the bodies after they die for love?

438
00:17:13,759 --> 00:17:15,460
You have a terrible way with words.

439
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:15,759
What?

440
00:17:15,759 --> 00:17:17,519
Why collect bodies?

441
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:19,880
Nowadays it's called one-stop funeral services.

442
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:20,640
Get lost.

443
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:21,880
No, I...

444
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:23,339
Grandma, sorry about that.

445
00:17:32,039 --> 00:17:33,900
What are you doing?

446
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:37,900
The big moon of Verona

447
00:17:38,180 --> 00:17:41,640
Balcony sweet talk is truly great

448
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:44,960
Ximen-meo and Juliet

449
00:17:45,079 --> 00:17:46,720
Tonight there will be

450
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:47,640
a new

451
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,500
a new sit

452
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,640
a new situation

453
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:51,359
Stop a moment

454
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:54,440
Director Hans says he has a headache

455
00:17:54,660 --> 00:17:56,599
Could it be a migraine?

456
00:17:57,180 --> 00:17:58,539
I have some herbal patches

457
00:17:58,539 --> 00:17:59,700
One stick and it works like a charm

458
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,200
Just don't know if a German

459
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,400
believes in our Chinese medicine

460
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:03,259
No

461
00:18:03,299 --> 00:18:04,640
It's not a headache, it's...

462
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:06,940
His head is a bit messy

463
00:18:07,259 --> 00:18:08,279
Head messy?

464
00:18:08,279 --> 00:18:10,400
You mean his hair is messy, right?

465
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:10,720
No

466
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:12,480
He says his mind is a mess

467
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:13,420
Really? Yes

468
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,819
His mind is a mess because of these

469
00:18:15,819 --> 00:18:16,400
What?

470
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:17,759
*Romance of the West Chamber*

471
00:18:17,759 --> 00:18:19,059
Ximen Qing and whatnot

472
00:18:19,059 --> 00:18:20,380
And that "West Wind" stuff

473
00:18:20,380 --> 00:18:21,680
It's just too "West"

474
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:24,579
He wanted Chinese elements!

475
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:26,859
Didn't you say "When in Rome, do as the Romans do"?

476
00:18:26,859 --> 00:18:28,000
Exactly

477
00:18:28,180 --> 00:18:29,160
He did say that

478
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,759
But Director Hans now

479
00:18:30,759 --> 00:18:32,599
feels something is wrong again

480
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:35,319
Can't say exactly what

481
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,000
I know what's wrong

482
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:38,920
What's your brilliant idea?

483
00:18:39,220 --> 00:18:40,299
These past few days

484
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,500
I've browsed through a few more books

485
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:45,319
gathered wisdom from many experts

486
00:18:45,319 --> 00:18:47,039
and did some deep meditation

487
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:48,640
Regarding this play of ours

488
00:18:48,779 --> 00:18:51,680
I have some further thoughts

489
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,440
That comrade asks: what thoughts?

490
00:18:53,539 --> 00:18:54,400
Who asked?

491
00:18:54,559 --> 00:18:55,799
Which comrade asked?

492
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,299
Well, our ancestors

493
00:18:58,299 --> 00:18:59,779
didn't they have a saying?

494
00:19:00,099 --> 00:19:00,920
Old people falling in love

495
00:19:00,940 --> 00:19:02,859
is like an old house on fire—beyond saving

496
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:04,460
Did our ancestors

497
00:19:04,819 --> 00:19:06,200
have that saying?

498
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,000
If the professor says so, let's assume they did

499
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:09,380
No

500
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:10,579
what's your point?

501
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,279
My point is

502
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:13,240
since

503
00:19:13,619 --> 00:19:15,480
old Romeo and old Juliet

504
00:19:15,759 --> 00:19:18,380
are a flammable, explosive old house

505
00:19:18,819 --> 00:19:20,599
when handling their relationship

506
00:19:21,279 --> 00:19:22,599
we can't do it like before

507
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:25,079
like typical twilight romance works

508
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:25,980
What do you want to do?

509
00:19:26,559 --> 00:19:28,079
Specifically for this scene

510
00:19:28,339 --> 00:19:29,259
I'm thinking

511
00:19:29,519 --> 00:19:30,819
I rush forward

512
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,220
and with Juliet

513
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:33,940
do a princess carry

514
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,319
No, what are you doing?

515
00:19:35,359 --> 00:19:36,259
That's a bit much

516
00:19:36,259 --> 00:19:38,220
I reckon my arm strength isn't enough

517
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:39,559
Might not be able to lift her

518
00:19:40,119 --> 00:19:40,839
Reckon what?

519
00:19:40,839 --> 00:19:42,359
You definitely can't lift her!

520
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,920
With that frame of yours

521
00:19:44,059 --> 00:19:46,019
you definitely can't do a carry

522
00:19:46,119 --> 00:19:47,319
A piggyback is more like it

523
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:48,700
Is a piggyback appropriate?

524
00:19:48,859 --> 00:19:50,539
Wouldn't that be rude to the beauty?

525
00:19:52,339 --> 00:19:53,220
What's wrong with a piggyback?

526
00:19:53,220 --> 00:19:54,619
In our traditional Chinese opera

527
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,880
isn't there a scene called "Pigsy Carries His Wife"?

528
00:19:57,599 --> 00:19:58,660
Chinese elements!

529
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:00,279
Now you're being even more ridiculous

530
00:20:00,319 --> 00:20:02,400
Then why call it *Romeo and Juliet*?

531
00:20:03,039 --> 00:20:03,819
Just call it

532
00:20:03,859 --> 00:20:05,119
*Romeo and Pigsy*

533
00:20:06,599 --> 00:20:07,779
That's a great name!

534
00:20:07,980 --> 00:20:08,779
Director Hans

535
00:20:08,819 --> 00:20:09,680
our play

536
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,359
how about we change the name to that?

537
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:13,279
No

538
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,799
Oh God, I can't take it anymore!

539
00:20:15,799 --> 00:20:16,299
Oh God, I can't take it anymore!

540
00:20:18,539 --> 00:20:19,980
He seems a bit reluctant

541
00:20:19,980 --> 00:20:21,400
That kid turned on us

542
00:20:21,559 --> 00:20:22,599
With whom?

543
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:25,220
He just left like that?

544
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:26,660
He just dropped it and quit?

545
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:27,259
Yes

546
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:30,519
What's going on here?

547
00:20:30,519 --> 00:20:31,359
Hello, elders

548
00:20:31,839 --> 00:20:33,119
Where is our Director Hans?

549
00:20:33,980 --> 00:20:34,759
He left

550
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:37,660
He left our retirement community

551
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:38,599
Why?

552
00:20:39,119 --> 00:20:39,799
He said

553
00:20:40,319 --> 00:20:42,019
working with you all

554
00:20:42,079 --> 00:20:42,920
is too tiring

555
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:43,740
His head

556
00:20:44,099 --> 00:20:45,619
is a mess

557
00:20:45,759 --> 00:20:46,720
No, but he

558
00:20:46,799 --> 00:20:48,000
just abandoned us?

559
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,859
That's right

560
00:20:49,359 --> 00:20:51,660
He went to Xincheng Kindergarten

561
00:20:52,579 --> 00:20:54,099
My grandson goes there

562
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:55,680
He said

563
00:20:56,039 --> 00:20:58,539
he'd rather go help the kids

564
00:20:58,619 --> 00:21:00,099
rehearse Romeo and Juliet

565
00:21:00,579 --> 00:21:02,700
We're worse than a bunch of little kids?

566
00:21:04,059 --> 00:21:05,819
I need to take leave and go check it out

567
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:07,059
If I can pull some strings

568
00:21:07,059 --> 00:21:08,539
maybe get my Doudou picked

569
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:09,240
Xiao Cai, come back

570
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:09,740
Okay

571
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:11,720
We Chinese have backbone

572
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:12,819
We don't beg for help

573
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,140
No, but

574
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,599
what do we do now? What do we do?

575
00:21:16,599 --> 00:21:16,980
Come on

576
00:21:17,539 --> 00:21:18,380
We'll rehearse it ourselves

577
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:19,240
I'll be the director

578
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,279
Old Li

579
00:21:20,299 --> 00:21:21,400
You continue as Romeo

580
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:21,680
You direct it

581
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,559
Ms. Liu, Juliet

582
00:21:22,559 --> 00:21:23,220
Alright

583
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,140
Xiao Cai

584
00:21:24,140 --> 00:21:24,660
Matchmaker

585
